"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-05-03-ecl-unai-emery-explains-why-aston-lost-4-2-to-olympiakos\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Aston Villa manager, Unai Emery, has given reason his team were beaten 4-2 against Olympiakos in the first leg of their Europa Conference League, ECL, semi-final on Thursday .  Ayoub El Kaabi's hat-trick ensured Olympiakos stunned Aston Villa at Villa Park.  Ollie Watkins and Moussa Diaby did score for Emery's side during the encounter.  Speaking after the game, Emery said Aston Villa did not play well against the visitors, adding that they did not have control of the game.  \\\"We are frustrated and disappointed, we did not play well,\\\" Emery said at his post-match interview.  \\\"This is the summary I can do at the beginning. We did not have control of the game. We were playing so fast.  \\\"In a lot of moments we needed to stop them getting good positions and get into their box with more passes than one, two or three. And they were attacking, playing so open. Our plan was completely different.  \\\"Congratulations, they deserve to win the first leg. We will try to come back but, of course, they are now favourites. We will play there and try to show something different to tonight.\\\"  The return leg will take place next week.  Ilechukwu backs Finidi to succeed with Super Eagles  EPL: Man Utd receive double injury boost ahead of Crystal Palace trip  EPL: Unai Emery names team that will not finish in top 5 after Villa lose to Everton  EPL: Why I did not shake hands with Mikel Arteta after Arsenal's 4-1 win - Villa boss, Unai Emery  EPL: Why Aston Villa lost 4-1 to Arsenal - Unai Emery  EPL: Why we beat Arsenal - Aston Villa manager Unai Emery  EPL: Unai Emery names favourites to win title ahead of Aston Villa vs Arsenal  ECL final: We played together - Maresca singles out one Real Betis player  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"